<m0>   <m0>Baywatch<m0>  star <m0>David Hasselhoff <m0>and his wife, actress <m0>Pamela Bach-Hasselhoff, <m0>have purchased the Encino, Calif. home of actor <m0>John Goodman <m0>for $1.5 million, sources say.<ep>
   The asking price on the 1.5-acre estate had been about $2.5 million. Goodman bought it in 1991 for just under $3 million, sources say.<ep>
   Built in 1988, the five-bedroom 6,000-square-foot compound includes a Colonial-style mansion, two guest houses, a tennis court, pool and spa. The home also has a pub room, gym, library and office.<ep>
   Goodman, 43, is said to have a home in another state. In December, he announced that he would make only guest appearances on <m0>Roseanne,<m0>  renewed for a ninth season.<ep>
   Hasselhoff, 43, is the highest-paid actor on syndicated television, sources say. Besides starring in <m0>Baywatch<m0>  and its spinoff <m0>Baywatch Nights,<m0>  he is one of the shows' four executive producers. When NBC dumped <m0>Baywatch<m0>  after a one-year run starting in 1989, Hasselhoff and his friends bought and produced the show, selling it to European syndicators and a U.S. distributor.<ep>
   The network hadn't realized what a hit the series was in Europe, but Hasselhoff knew and realized its potential, having become a successful pop singer there after his series <m0>Knight Rider <m0>was canceled in 1986.<ep>
   <m0>Baywatch<m0> now airs in more than 140 countries and is seen by one billion viewers a week.<ep>
   A philanthropist who will be honored in June as the L.A. Make-a-Wish Foundation's Man of the Year, Hasselhoff is a businessman; he launched a line of <m0>Baywatch<m0> products, including swimsuits, and has plans for a series of <m0>Baywatch<m0> theme restaurants, sources say.<ep>
   Bach-Hasselhoff, 30, also appears in <m0>Baywatch,<m0>  playing a former TV reporter who runs a beachfront cafe.<ep>
   The Hasselhoffs, married since 1989, have two children and have been living in Sherman Oaks, Calif.<m1><ql>
