<m0>   <m0>Dinah Shore's <m0>Beverly Hills home has been sold to a Beverly Hills couple, a plastic surgeon and a businesswoman, for just under $3 million, sources say.<ep>
   The house, Shore's residence for nearly 30 years, first went on the market in July 1994, five months after the popular entertainer died there at age 76. The original asking price was $4.2 million.<ep>
   Built in 1949, the 10,000-square-foot seven-bedroom home, on nearly an acre behind the Beverly Hills Hotel, has a tennis court, two-bedroom guest house, gym and office.<ql>
