   Linn-Baker, who made his film debut starring with <m0>Peter O'Toole <m0>in <m0>My Favorite Year<m0> (1982), co-stars with Nathan Lane (<m0>The Birdcage <m0>) in the Broadway revival of <m0>A Funny Thing Happened on the Way to the Forum.<m0> Lobel has designed sets for such Broadway productions as the 1994 Sondheim and Lapine musical <m0>Passion.<m0> <ep>
   Linn-Baker, 42, and Lobel were married last June, just after he purchased the Hollywood home from actor <m0>John Hillerman. <m0>Lobel was living in New York. Now they're both living there. Linn-Baker has appeared in other Broadway plays and he is a founding director of the New York Stage and Film Co., which developed the one-man show <m0>Tru.<m0><ep>
   The home has city views, three bedrooms, a maid's room, loft, screening room and separate gym. The 8,000-square-foot estate also has a pool and spa.<ql>
